<subSubSection id="EAB51EEA12883646738AC5A3D6B29A04" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="5B456359F205DCD50DDAF10BA23108E1" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="32980CB10836EB49F4E5A858EEC745E7" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">
Roadside, burned over cloud forest on steep south-facing slope; shrub 
<normalizedToken id="9AB5255DE7C43FAD5954CBE52441EE54" originalValue="páramo">paramo</normalizedToken>
at 2400-3000 m in elevation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="77F5FA48D787F3298D0AC9E0B15260C6" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">
The species is the most commonly collected member of the genus but apparently is sympatric with both 
<taxonomicName id="81F6380FEA23ECDF4F3A52D4F3258315" authorityName="H. Rob. &amp; V. A. Funk" authorityYear="2012" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cuatrecasanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kingii">
<emphasis id="A7A11B18A97101D9E844F61118C70F08" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Cuatrecasanthus kingii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="933D53FA9C3BA5A95D2DBEB843EA469C" authorityName="H. Rob. &amp; V. A. Funk" authorityYear="2012" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cuatrecasanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanceolatus">
<emphasis id="FF3CE5F86ADC6BED3981AE99EB6636D3" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Cuatrecasanthus lanceolatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the area near the border between Loja and Zamora/Chinchipe. The species is very closely related to the northern Peruvian 
<taxonomicName id="A988F14F7FE8A3151CD2F42E988280EA" authorityName="H. Rob" authorityYear="1989" baseAuthorityName="Hieron." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cuatrecasanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jelskii">
<emphasis id="97C582F4F7FC9DA5AE034017FAD8167A" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Cuatrecasanthus jelskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hieron.) H. Rob. The latter differs most obviously by the densely hirsute abaxial surface of the midvein of the leaves and erect rather than appressed trichomes of the abaxial blade surface. The adaxial leaf surface of the latter also has less strongly insculpate veins.
</paragraph>
